summary:
Amit Kumar is a dynamic Product Leader with over 12 years of experience in driving innovation and executing strategic product initiatives within the technology sector. He holds a Postgraduate Diploma in Management (PGDM) with a specialization in Marketing and Strategic Management from the Institute of Management Technology, Ghaziabad, and a Bachelor of Engineering in Electronics and Communications from Manipal Institute of Technology. His educational foundation includes coursework in Digital Marketing, Strategic Management, Artificial Intelligence, and Database Management.

Amit has held key positions such as Co-founder & Director at Happy People AI, where he leads the technological vision and strategy, fostering growth through innovation and cross-functional collaboration. Previously, he served as Product Manager at Aljazeera Media House, driving a 30% increase in user engagement through product development aligned with market needs. His experience also includes roles as Product Delivery Manager at Nowfloats Technology Limited and Senior Analyst at Accenture Services Pvt. Ltd., where he honed his skills in project management, SAP technology, and client relationships.

Amit possesses a robust skill set in Product Strategy, Digital Marketing, User Engagement Analytics, and Market Research, with technical proficiency in tools like JIRA and Cloud technologies. He is a Certified Scrum Product Owner (CSPO), emphasizing his knowledge in Agile methodologies.

Fluent in Hindi and English, with conversational skills in Spanish, Amit is recognized for his leadership, communication, and problem-solving abilities. He actively supports causes in mentoring, environmental issues, and education. Open to opportunities that leverage his expertise in innovative product solutions, he is based in Hyderabad, India, and can be reached at amit@happypeopleai.com.

Naheeda Afreen is a dynamic Full Stack Developer with 9 months of experience specializing in innovative solutions and seamless user experiences. She holds a Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Information Technology from CVR College of Engineering, along with a Higher Secondary Certificate in Science from Sri Gayatri Junior College. During her academic journey, she engaged in projects such as a Student Attendance Monitoring System and a chatbot for college applications, showcasing her ability to integrate technology into real-world applications.

Naheeda's professional experience includes internships as an Android Developer at Vyza Solutions and a Software Engineer Intern at Happy People AI, where she contributed to the development of an Android application and a project leveraging ReactJS and Node.js. Her technical expertise spans Java, HTML/CSS, JavaScript, SQL, and React, with advanced proficiency in coding and application design. Naheeda's practical knowledge is reinforced by certifications, including Oracle Certified Associate in Java SE 8 and Database Programming with SQL.

In addition to her technical skills, Naheeda has demonstrated leadership and adaptability through various roles and volunteer experiences, earning accolades such as the Best Student Award during her studies. She is fluent in English and Hindi, enhancing her communication skills in collaborative environments.

Naheeda is seeking full-time roles as a Software Engineer, Full Stack Developer, or Java Developer, ideally within product management or information technology sectors. She is open to hybrid, onsite, or remote opportunities, prefers to work in Hyderabad, and has an expected salary of ₹500,000 annually. Her proactive approach to problem-solving and commitment to continuous learning make her a valuable candidate for tech-driven organizations.

Arunkumar K is a motivated AI Intern with over seven months of hands-on experience, specializing in machine learning, natural language processing, and generative AI technologies. He holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science from Bharathidasan University and is currently pursuing a Post Graduate Diploma in Data Science from the Central University of Tamil Nadu, where he has enhanced his skills in machine learning and big data technologies through rigorous coursework and practical projects.

Arunkumar has gained significant expertise through his internships at Telic Info Services Pvt Ltd and Happy People AI, where he contributed to the development of AI-driven applications and machine learning models. His key responsibilities included assisting in predictive analytics, data analysis, and the deployment of AI solutions on cloud platforms like AWS Lambda. Furthermore, he has actively participated in projects that leverage cutting-edge AI technologies and has developed innovative systems, such as a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) based chatbot tailored for Tamil language users.

Proficient in Python, SQL, and various data visualization tools, Arunkumar possesses a robust technical skill set, complemented by his ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and communicate ideas clearly. He is recognized for his achievements, including securing first place in a national-level quiz competition and successfully presenting a research paper on generative AI in a reputed journal.

Fluent in English and Tamil, Arunkumar is seeking full-time employment opportunities in the information technology sector, specifically in roles such as AI Engineer or Machine Learning Engineer. He is open to hybrid, on-site, or remote work arrangements with a preferred location in Chennai, Coimbatore, or Bangalore. He anticipates an annual salary of INR 500,000 and has a notice period of 30 days, with a readiness to travel or relocate as required.

Venkata Ramani Krishna is an innovative UI/UX Designer with a Bachelor’s degree in Electronics and Communication from QIS College of Engineering and Technology, where he honed his skills in circuit design, embedded systems, and communication networks. With seven months of practical experience, he has excelled as a Design Intern at Happy People AI and previously as a UI/UX Designer at Zenith Yuga, where he played a pivotal role in enhancing user experiences through user research, wireframing, and prototyping. His notable projects include the development of an event booking platform and a bus ticket application, showcasing his ability to merge design with functionality effectively.

Venkata possesses a diverse skill set, including expertise in responsive design, interaction design, and user research, utilizing tools such as Figma, Adobe XD, Sketch, and InVision. He holds certifications in UI/UX design from Great Learning and Elearn Info Tech, further underscoring his commitment to professional growth. His portfolio includes innovative projects that illustrate his design capabilities, such as an agricultural robot and various responsive web applications. 

Fluent in Hindi, Telugu, and English, he is recognized for his strong communication, teamwork, and problem-solving skills. Venkata is actively seeking full-time opportunities as a UI/UX Designer or Software Engineer in the software and computing industries, with a preference for remote or hybrid working models. He is available to join immediately and is open to relocation, aiming for an expected annual salary of ₹10,00,000.

Sourabh Purwar is a seasoned UX leader and Co-Founder & Director of Happy People AI, boasting over 10 years of experience in building and leading multi-disciplinary international teams centered on user experience and service design. He earned an MBA in Marketing and Business Research from the Institute of Management Technology, Ghaziabad, and a Bachelor of Arts in Animation and Multimedia from Birla Institute of Technology, Mesra, where he honed his design thinking skills. 

In his recent tenure as a Senior Consultant at Deloitte, Sourabh excelled in driving innovation and product strategy projects for Fortune 500 clients, emphasizing user-centric design and operational excellence. He previously led the UX research team at Oracle Netsuite, managing localization projects and implementing data-driven insights that significantly improved product performance. His earlier roles include establishing the UX Center of Excellence at ACS Group and overseeing content creation as Operation and Design Manager at Sterling Publishers.

Sourabh is proficient in UX Design, Product Management, and Strategic Planning, utilizing tools such as Figma and Adobe Creative Suite at an expert level. His commitment to continual learning is evident through certifications in data-driven UX research and usability. He has published articles on UX design and has a proven track record of mentoring emerging designers and leading teams to success, achieving notable accolades including winning the “Buildathon for Good” with Oracle Netsuite.

Fluent in English and Hindi, Sourabh actively seeks opportunities in dynamic environments, preferring remote or hybrid work arrangements with a focus on the start-up, MSME, or corporate sectors. He is open to travel and is eager to contribute to impactful projects that enhance user engagement and satisfaction.

Tulasi Subrahmanyam is a dynamic and motivated MERN Stack Developer with over a year of hands-on experience in both frontend and backend technologies. Currently working as a Full Stack Developer for Happy People AI, Tulasi contributes to the development of Project Riseon, focusing on designing responsive front-end features and building robust back-end systems leveraging modern technologies like ReactJS, Node.js, and Supabase. Previously, Tulasi served as a Full Stack Intern at Vivid Wizards and a Frontend Developer Intern at Viscommerce, where he honed his skills in creating engaging web applications and integrating advanced features.

Tulasi holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science from Sri Sai Degree College, where he completed coursework in data structures, algorithms, and software engineering. He also participated in coding competitions and developed a web-based application as a capstone project. His technical proficiency includes JavaScript, HTML/CSS, RESTful APIs, and tools like Git, Visual Studio Code, and JIRA.

He possesses certifications in Full Stack Web Development and JavaScript, further enhancing his technical foundation. Noteworthy projects include the Hotel Booking Project and the Ecommerce App, both showcasing his ability to implement secure user authentication and optimize user experience through innovative design.

Fluent in English and Telugu, Tulasi excels in communication and collaboration, coupled with strong problem-solving abilities. He is seeking full-time opportunities as a Software Engineer or Full Stack Developer in the Information Technology or Product Management sectors, preferably in Chennai, Hyderabad, or Bengaluru, with an expected salary of INR 550,000 annually. Tulasi is available to join immediately and is open to onsite, remote, or hybrid work arrangements.

Shivek Soni is a dedicated Full Stack Developer with over a year of experience specializing in building robust, scalable, and user-centric web applications. He holds a Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering from the National Institute of Technology Hamirpur, where he completed an extensive curriculum covering programming languages such as C, C++, Java, and Python, along with key subjects like Data Structures, Algorithms, and Database Management Systems.

Currently employed as a Full Stack Developer at Happy People AI, Shivek actively contributes to the development of innovative projects, including Project Riseon, where he designs responsive front-end features using ReactJS and implements a dynamic back-end with Node.js. His technical proficiency extends to database management with Supabase, integration of RESTful APIs, and application of AI-based functionalities. He has also completed intensive training in Full Stack Web Development, gaining practical knowledge in utilizing modern frameworks and best practices in coding.

Shivek's skill set includes advanced proficiency in React, Node.js, and JavaScript, alongside intermediate experience with tools like Git, Docker, and Postman. He has been recognized for his exceptional performance in team settings, demonstrating strong problem-solving abilities, effective communication, and adaptability.

Shivek is eager to explore opportunities in large corporates and startups within the engineering industry, preferring hybrid or remote work arrangements. He seeks a full-time role with an expected annual salary of ₹1,200,000 and is open to relocating. With a passion for continuous learning and innovative solutions, Shivek is committed to making a significant impact in the tech landscape.

Shalini Sharma is a dedicated Full Stack Developer with nearly 2 years of experience specializing in the design and development of responsive, user-friendly web applications. She holds a Bachelor's degree in Information Technology from Narula Institute of Technology, where she gained solid foundational knowledge in key subjects such as Computer Science and Mathematics. Shalini's work experience encompasses significant roles, including her current position at Happy People AI, where she is tasked with creating seamless user experiences through both front-end and back-end development. Previously, she honed her skills as an HTML Developer at Bayshore Intelligence Solutions and Quadrant Labs, where she optimized web performance and collaborated effectively with cross-functional teams.

Proficient in JavaScript, React, Node.js, SQL, and HTML/CSS, Shalini utilizes her technical expertise to deliver scalable solutions while ensuring code quality and best practices in web development. She is adept with tools such as Git, JIRA, and Postman, contributing to efficient project management and collaboration. Her commitment to continuous learning is demonstrated through various certifications, including AWS and Java Basic from HackerRank.

Shalini has successfully completed notable projects like "Mega Blog," a dynamic application utilizing React.js and Supabase, and her personal portfolio website, showcasing her ability to create visually appealing and functional web applications. She has been recognized as a "Performer in the making" at Bayshore Intelligence Solutions, reflecting her strong work ethic and potential.

Fluent in English and Hindi, Shalini possesses excellent communication, problem-solving, and collaboration skills. She seeks a full-time position as a Full Stack Developer, with a preference for hybrid working arrangements. Shalini is open to opportunities in MSME or large corporate environments and is willing to travel as needed, with a notice period of 30 days.

Vivek Gupta is a dynamic Full Stack Developer with over a year of experience specializing in building scalable web applications. He holds a dual degree in Electronics & Communication Engineering from the National Institute of Technology, Hamirpur, where he engaged in projects involving cloud-based systems and advanced algorithms. His academic journey commenced with a strong foundation in science from Subhash BVM Sr. Sec. School, where he excelled in problem-solving and developed an affinity for technology.

Vivek's professional experience includes his recent role at Happy People AI, where he significantly enhanced user engagement by 30% through the implementation of innovative web solutions and effective collaboration with cross-functional teams. Previously, during his internship at eZ Technology LLC, he optimized RESTful APIs using Node.js and Express, leading to improved system efficiency and database performance.

Recognized for his outstanding performance in Data Structures and Algorithms, and ranking in the top 1.6% in the JEE Main examination, Vivek combines technical expertise with strong interpersonal skills such as problem-solving, adaptability, and effective communication. Fluent in both English and Hindi, he is now seeking innovative opportunities in the IT sector, particularly in leadership and strategy development roles. Expected to graduate in May 2024, Sai has built expertise through coursework in Neural Networks and AWS Cloud Technical Essentials, while actively participating in projects that demonstrate technical acumen and collaborative skills. 

Currently working at Happy People AI, Sai has successfully developed and maintained APIs for Large Language Models, resulting in a notable 25% increase in API usage. Previously, as a Machine Learning Intern at HRH Next Services Limited, he improved model efficiency by 20% through data analysis and CI/CD pipeline implementation. 

Proficient in Python, AWS, and Natural Language Processing, Sai has also engaged in innovative projects like Smart Agro Nexus and Jarvis - Virtual Assistant, showcasing skills in API development and blockchain integration for agricultural solutions. His publication on AI-powered agricultural solutions highlights his commitment to leveraging technology for sustainable practices. Recognized with awards such as First Position in Mini-Project Expo, Sai combines technical capabilities with strong interpersonal skills, including problem-solving and adaptability.

He is fluent in English and Telugu, enhancing his communication in diverse environments. Looking forward, Sai seeks full-time or contractual opportunities in machine learning or data science roles within the Information Technology industry, preferably in Hyderabad, Bangalore, or Chennai, with an expected annual salary of ₹1,200,000. His availability aligns with a flexible work schedule and a willingness to relocate for career growth.

Priyanka Panchal is an aspiring Quality Engineer with over 6 years of experience in the IT sector, specializing in quality engineering and software testing. She holds a Bachelor’s degree in Computer Engineering from Silver Oak College of Engineering & Technology, where she actively participated in coding competitions and developed a mobile application for campus navigation. Additionally, she earned a Diploma in Computer Engineering from R.C Technical Institute, which included hands-on projects like a library management system.

Throughout her career, Priyanka has gained valuable experience in various roles, including Subject Matter Expert at RevoKarmaHub Software and Services Pvt. Ltd., where she enhanced project efficiency by analyzing data for marketplaces and developing testing strategies. Currently, she serves as a Quality Engineering intern at Happy People AI, focusing on executing test cases, identifying defects, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure high-quality software products. Her past involvement as a Trainee Software Tester and Quality Analyst Intern has further honed her skills in functional testing, defect tracking, and test case development.

Priyanka is proficient in manual testing methodologies and tools such as TestLink, Mantis, and Azure DevOps, with a strong command of functional and black box testing. She holds a certification in Manual Testing from Unicode Technologies and has published a research paper in the International Journal of Quality Engineering on enhancing software quality through rigorous testing processes. 

Fluent in both English and Hindi, Priyanka is recognized for her analytical thinking, problem-solving abilities, and teamwork. She seeks full-time opportunities as a Quality Analyst or Engineer in the Information Technology or Communications industries, preferably in Vadodara or remote settings, with an expected salary of 20,000 INR per month.

She specializes in optimizing capital structures and securing funding solutions, particularly in the investment banking sector with a strong focus on mergers and acquisitions. Shubhra holds a Master of Business Administration in Finance from Goethe University Frankfurt and a Bachelor of Commerce in Accounting and Finance from the University of Mumbai, where she also completed a noteworthy dissertation on risk assessment in emerging markets. 

Her professional journey includes significant roles as a Financial Analyst at PwC and a Junior Financial Analyst at KPMG, where she developed impactful financial reports and contributed to strategic financial planning. Shubhra has demonstrated her capacity to drive growth through advanced financial modeling and meticulous risk assessments, earning her recognition as the Top Performer in Debt Advisory at Deloitte for structuring over €500 million in financing arrangements. She is also distinguished with the Excellence in Financial Modeling award from the Institute of Financial Analysts.

Shubhra's technical skills encompass advanced proficiency in financial modeling, strategic advisory, and capital structure optimization, complemented by her adeptness in tools like Excel and Tableau. Fluent in both English and German, she possesses strong interpersonal skills, particularly in communication, teamwork, and client relationship management. With aspirations to further engage in investment banking and equity analysis, Shubhra seeks new opportunities in Frankfurt Am Main, where she can leverage her expertise to foster financial growth while maintaining a focus on environmental conservation and youth education causes.

Currently serving as the General Manager of Credit Monitoring and Recovery at NKGSB Co-operative Bank Ltd, he excels in overseeing strategic management of credit portfolios, ensuring compliance with regulatory standards, and optimizing recovery processes. Prior to this role, he held significant positions, including Head of Credit for Business Banking and Retail Banking, where he developed comprehensive credit policies that enhanced customer satisfaction and streamlined operations.

Upendra holds a Master of Business Administration in Finance from Jamnalal Bajaj Institute of Management Studies, complemented by a Bachelor of Commerce in Accountancy from the University of Mumbai. His educational background is further enhanced by numerous certifications, including Certified Risk Management Professional and Advanced Credit Risk Management, showcasing his commitment to continuous learning in the field.

His robust skill set includes advanced proficiency in credit risk analysis, financial modeling, and regulatory compliance, underpinned by technical tools such as Excel, SAS, and Tableau. Upendra is recognized for his leadership, negotiation, and team-building skills, contributing to a collaborative work environment. His contributions to the industry have been acknowledged with awards like Best Practices in Risk Management from the Reserve Bank of India.

Passionate about environmental conservation and education for the underprivileged, Upendra is also an avid photographer and cyclist. He is open to exploring directorial roles in product management and banking in Mumbai. With a proven track record of enhancing credit portfolios and risk mitigation strategies, he is poised to make significant contributions in the banking sector.

Swapna Shenvi is a dynamic HR professional with over four years of experience specializing in enhancing employee experience and implementing comprehensive recruitment strategies across both technical and non-technical domains. She holds a Master of Business Administration in Human Resource Management from The Vedica Scholars Programme for Women, complemented by a Bachelor of Commerce specializing in Business Administration from Mithibai Motiram Kundnani College of Commerce & Economics. Throughout her academic journey, she actively participated in HR case studies and simulated environments, contributing to her robust understanding of strategic HR practices.

In her professional capacity, Swapna has held significant roles, including HR Manager at Happy People AI, where she effectively managed recruitment processes, developed strategies to attract top talent, and analyzed workforce metrics to enhance recruitment and retention strategies. As a Skilling Analyst at Disprz, she utilized HR analytics to derive actionable insights, resulting in a 15% increase in operational efficiency. Her early career includes impactful roles as an HR Intern at ASK Group and as an Agency Development Manager at Max Life Insurance, where she honed her skills in employee engagement and talent management.

Swapna possesses strong technical skills in talent acquisition, employee development, and HR analytics, alongside advanced proficiency in various HR tools such as ATS and HRIS software. She is recognized for her interpersonal skills, particularly in communication, empathy, and adaptability, which bolster her effectiveness in team leadership and conflict resolution.

Recently awarded a Prime Minister's Certificate for outstanding contribution to yoga education, she is also conversational in English, Hindi, and Marathi. Swapna is currently seeking opportunities in HR management or talent acquisition roles in Hyderabad, with a preference for organizations that value a high-performance culture and employee engagement.

Mainak Chaudhuri is an innovative Software Engineer with nearly two years of experience, currently employed at Happy People AI, where he has made significant contributions in developing scalable software solutions for the automotive and aerospace sectors. His expertise lies in leveraging machine learning and data analysis to enhance user experiences and optimize performance. He holds a Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering from the prestigious Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur, with a strong focus on software development, algorithms, and data structures. 

His professional journey began with a pivotal internship at Tech Innovators Inc., where he gained hands-on experience in software development and data-driven strategies. Mainak has consistently demonstrated his technical acumen by implementing machine learning models and conducting comprehensive data analyses to drive strategic decision-making within teams. 

In addition to his technical skills in machine learning, data analysis, software development, and performance optimization, he is proficient in tools such as TensorFlow, Pandas, and Git. Mainak has earned certifications, including a Machine Learning Specialization from Stanford University and a Data Science Professional Certificate from Harvard University, further solidifying his expertise. He is also a published author, contributing to leading journals on optimizing performance through machine learning and enhancing data analytics in the aerospace sector.

Recognized for his innovative software development at Happy People AI, he received the Excellence in Data-Driven Engineering award for his impactful contributions. Fluent in both English and Bengali, Mainak possesses strong interpersonal skills, including team collaboration, problem-solving, and critical thinking. He is currently seeking opportunities in software engineering focused on data-driven solutions in a dynamic environment, ideally within Kolkata.

Smita Garg is an accomplished Principal Engineer with over 13 years of experience in software development and engineering leadership, specializing in creating innovative technology solutions. She has demonstrated her expertise at renowned companies, including Dell EMC, Oracle, and PTC. In her current role at Dell EMC, Smita leads engineering teams to develop high-performance software systems, aligning project outcomes with strategic business objectives and driving projects from conception to completion. Her previous experience as a Senior Software Engineer at Oracle involved designing software architectures and optimizing system performance to meet enterprise-level requirements.

Smita holds certifications in Advanced Software Architecture and as a Certified ScrumMaster (CSM), which underscores her commitment to continuous learning and agile project management. She has also contributed to reputable publications, such as the IEEE Software journal and international conferences, highlighting advancements in software engineering and microservices architecture.

Her technical skills encompass advanced proficiency in tools like JIRA and Git, alongside solid experience with Docker and Kubernetes. Smita excels in leadership, collaboration, and problem-solving, fostering a culture of mentorship among her peers. Recognized with the Excellence in Engineering Award from Dell EMC, she successfully deployed AI chatbot solutions that boosted customer engagement by 30%.

Fluent in English and Hindi, Smita is actively seeking opportunities as a Staff Engineer, Engineering Manager, or Senior Principal Engineer, with a focus on roles that allow her to leverage her extensive expertise in software architecture and product management. She is open to positions in Bengaluru and is enthusiastic about further driving engineering excellence in her next role.

Pranjal Joshi is an accomplished Counselor with over four years of experience in the mental health sector, currently working at Yin Yang Healing in Jaipur, India. She holds a Master’s Degree in Counseling Psychology from Indira Gandhi National Open University, where she focused on therapeutic techniques, psychological assessment, and intervention strategies. Pranjal has completed advanced coursework in Cognitive Behavioral Therapy and Advanced Psychopathology, emphasizing her commitment to professional development.

During her internship at Mind Matters Clinic, Pranjal gained hands-on experience assisting lead counselors in therapy sessions, developing treatment plans, and facilitating group therapy. These roles have honed her skills in empathetic communication and active listening, which are complemented by her certifications, including Certified Professional Counselor (CPC) and Trauma-Informed Care Certification.

Pranjal's expertise extends to program development, crisis intervention, and client assessment, with a proven track record of implementing wellness programs that increased client engagement by 30%. She has authored a research article published in the International Journal of Counseling Psychology, showcasing her dedication to advancing the field.

Fluent in English and Hindi, Pranjal demonstrates strong problem-solving abilities and conflict resolution skills, making her an effective team collaborator. Her achievements include receiving the Counseling Excellence Award from the Indian Association for Clinical Psychologists.

Pranjal is open to opportunities that allow her to enhance client well-being within the mental health domain, preferring roles that value comprehensive care and teamwork in collaborative environments.
